            .</p>
               <p>CHARLES RICHARDSON. I am a <rs id="t18301209-250-viclabel1409" type="occupation">market-gardener</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-250-victim2102 t18301209-250-viclabel1409"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18301209-250-crimeloc1410">Isleworth</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-250-crimeloc1410" type="placeName" value="Isleworth"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18301209-250-crimeloc1410" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-250-off1407 t18301209-250-crimeloc1410"></join>. I lost these onions from a shed belonging to my house, on Friday last - they had been transferred from where I had left them, into a hay-loft, put into a sack, and partly concealed under hay-bands and other litter; the prisoner was my carter, and was going to town the same evening with me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-250-person2103">
                  HANNAH 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18301209-250-person2103" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-250-person2103" type="given" value="HANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-250-person2103" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Richardson. A little before one o'clock on Friday, I saw the prisoner put a prop against the hay-loft door, which I never saw before - I told my master I thought there was something wrong in the loft; I had seen the prisoner loading onions on the cart at five o'clock in the evening.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-250-person2104">
                  CHARLES 
                  RICHARDSON
               <interp inst="t18301209-250-person2104" type="surname" value="RICHARDSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-250-person2104" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-250-person2104" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I had the prisoner stopped with his cart, when he had got five hundred yards from my house, and I pretended I wanted a sovereign changed- I then found these onions.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. CHURCHILL. Q. These onions had been transferred from one part to another? A. Yes - he was employed to carry onions for sale, but he never took any to sell without my direction; I have generally been on the premises when he has loaded his cart - I have sometimes been in London, and he has brought the cart to me, but I prepare my own goods for<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183012090122"></xptr>market in a particular manner, and when they have been loaded he takes them - the shed was at the back of my premises.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. You have no doubt the onions were yours? A. No; I saw them at one o'clock, and saw them on the cart at five, in the same sack - the prisoner had 12s. a week, and 1s. a night when he went to market.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I do not know how they came on the cart.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18301209-250-verdict1411" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18301209-250-verdict1411" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19. - <rs id="t18301209-250-punish1412" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18301209-250-punish1412" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18301209-250-defend2100 t18301209-250-punish1412"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
